  "prompt": "How should I react when a girl says: I love you?",
  "response": "Here are some potential responses depending on your feelings:\n\n1. If you love her too:\n- \"I love you too\"\n- Say it back sincerely and genuinely\n- Express your feelings through words and actions\n\n2. If you're not sure or don't feel the same:\n- Be honest and kind\n- Don't say \"I love you\" if you don't mean it\n- Explain your feelings respectfully\n- Say something like \"I care about you deeply, but I'm not ready to say I love you\"\n\n3. If you don't have romantic feelings:\n- Be gentle and clear\n- Avoid leading her on\n- Explain that you value her as a friend/person\n- Be compassionate about her feelings\n\n4. General advice:\n- Stay calm and composed\n- Consider the context and timing\n- Be authentic\n- Communicate openly and respectfully\n\nThe most important thing is to be honest about your feelings while being kind and considerate of her emotions.",
